  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a wide-based pan (preferably non-stick)&nbsp;with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a low heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>sultanas</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked &ndash; this is your <strong>sultana rice</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve&nbsp;1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> of <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the<strong> onions</strong> have softened, add the <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>korma curry powder</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1578.-step-4-x200.jpg",
